</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C323E6F3FFB7D675E5E1FE5FFF35FE6E" pageId="27" pageNumber="178" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8B86B578FFB7D675E5E1FE5FFF35FE6E" blockId="27.[151,1437,152,971]" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">
<emphasis id="B94D696AFFB7D675E5E1FE5FFE8CFE12" bold="true" box="[199,334,405,431]" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name refers to this species’s association with host plant of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C39CEFBFFB7D675E03AFE5CFF35FE6E" authority="P. Browne." authorityName="P. Browne." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Varronia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="27" pageNumber="178" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B94D696AFFB7D675E03AFE5CFABDFE12" box="[1308,1407,406,431]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">Varronia</emphasis>
P. Browne.
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
