<subSubSection id="C323E6F3FFB7D675E5E1FCEAFACDFC76" pageId="27" pageNumber="178" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B86B578FFB7D675E5E1FCEAFACDFC76" blockId="27.[151,1437,152,971]" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">
<emphasis id="B94D696AFFB7D675E5E1FCEAFE8DFC86" bold="true" box="[199,335,800,827]" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">Comments.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C39CEFBFFB7D675E471FCEBFDA2FC86" authority="Monteiro &amp; Barbosa &amp; Esposito, 2019" authorityName="Monteiro &amp; Barbosa &amp; Esposito" authorityYear="2019" box="[343,608,801,827]" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Phytomyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="178" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="varronivora" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B94D696AFFB7D675E471FCEBFDA2FC86" box="[343,608,801,827]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">Phytomyza varronivora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A27ED411FFB7D675E74FFCEBFD01FC86" box="[617,707,801,827]" pageId="27" pageNumber="178" rank="species">
<emphasis id="B94D696AFFB7D675E74FFCEBFD01FC86" bold="true" box="[617,707,801,827]" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C39CEFBFFB7D675E67CFCEBFB0FFC86" authority="Zetterstedt" authorityName="Zetterstedt" authorityYear="1860" box="[858,1229,801,827]" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Phytomyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="178" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crassiseta">
<emphasis id="B94D696AFFB7D675E67CFCEBFB8EFC86" box="[858,1100,801,827]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">Phytomyza crassiseta</emphasis>
Zetterstedt
</taxonomicName>
due to the basally enlarged arista, but it is differentiated by the well-developed epandrium, occupying approximately half the length of the abdomen. The inner arms of the epandrium and the distiphallus are characteristics of this species and essentials for differentiating it from other 
<taxonomicName id="4C39CEFBFFB7D675E4DEFC47FDB1FC1A" authorityName="Fallen" authorityYear="1810" box="[504,627,909,935]" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Phytomyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="178" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B94D696AFFB7D675E4DEFC47FDB1FC1A" box="[504,627,909,935]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">Phytomyza</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species. Larvae forme serpentine mines on the leaf surface and pupation takes place on the ground. This is the first Agromyzdae species known to feed on 
<taxonomicName id="4C39CEFBFFB7D675E10DFC78FACDFC76" authority="P. Browne." authorityName="P. Browne." box="[1067,1295,945,971]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Varronia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="27" pageNumber="178" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B94D696AFFB7D675E10DFC78FB4CFC76" box="[1067,1166,946,971]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">Varronia</emphasis>
P. Browne.
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
